inspiracio.servlet.jsp
Class DummyPageContext

java.lang.Object
  javax.servlet.jsp.JspContext
      javax.servlet.jsp.PageContext
          inspiracio.servlet.jsp.DummyPageContext
Direct Known Subclasses:
ServletPageContext
public class DummyPageContext
extends PageContext

Superclass for PageContext implementations. This class gives the convenience methods and a basis for page scope. The rest of the methods throws new NotImplementedException("not implemented").

Author:
alex

removeAttribute

public void removeAttribute(String name,
                            int scope)
Remove the object reference associated with the specified name in the given scope. Does nothing if there is no such object. Simple implementation for page scope: subclass may want to override. For the other scopes, the implementation here is fine.

Specified by:
removeAttribute in class JspContext

JspContext.removeAttribute(java.lang.String, int)

setAttribute

public void setAttribute(String name,
                         Object value)
Simple implementation: subclass may want to override. Register the name and value specified with page scope semantics. If the value passed in is null, this has the same effect as calling removeAttribute( name, PageContext.PAGE_SCOPE ).

Specified by:
setAttribute in class JspContext
See Also:
